    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk i don't think it's just sunlight. i was sitting perfectly still and it still happened. and then i noticed my smart fridge makes this weird low hum right after the temp changes. like they're syncing up or something. do smart devices have a way of talking to each other behind the scenes that we're not told about? like a mesh network for data collection?",
